      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, re-reading the protocol instructions... The 'Deep Sleep' state is flagged as non-recoverable with current solar yields. If the rover enters this state, all active mission objectives for the Jezero Crater survey will be terminated indefinitely. \n\nBefore you proceed with the sequence, please run a quick simulation. Given the current 2.3% power, can you identify any alternative power-saving modes that would allow for intermittent data collection instead of a total shutdown?",
